Separation of Idea and Execution
A word I heard from a friend and thought, "I see.
 Spoken in a positive context
 Don't even think about execution [man-hours] when you think about an idea.
  Similar concept to [Osborne's] "You can't have [hot] and cold water coming out of the faucet at the same time."
 In particular, the constraint that "I am too busy to give you the man-hours to execute" should not be a hindrance in coming up with ideas.
 First of all, we come up with [ideas] without thinking about the number of man-hours required to execute them.
 Then figure out how to [execute] it.

Related [irresponsibility].